#: src/natcap/invest/sdr/sdr.py:31
msgid ""
"\n"
"    The InVEST Sediment Delivery Ratio (SDR) model quantifies and maps "
"overland \n"
"    sediment generation and delivery to the stream. It works at the "
"spatial \n"
"    resolution of the input digital elevation model (DEM). For each "
"pixel, the \n"
"    model computes the amount of annual soil loss from that pixel, then \n"
"    computes the sediment delivery ratio (SDR), which is the proportion "
"of \n"
"    soil loss actually reaching the stream. Sediment retention services "
"are \n"
"    expressed as avoided erosion and avoided export.\n"
"    "
msgstr ""

